document.full_text: the deal was struck in early april. two weeks after the u.n. security council vote that saved rebel-held benghazi from near-certain defeat, libya's ragtag rebels agreed to the first shipment of oil from the chunk of territory they held.
document.title: special report: in libyan oil shipment, sanctions prove dumb
